WEBVTT

00:02.341 --> 00:05.011
[ Rings]

00:05.094 --> 00:07.346
Honeydew! What's up?

00:07.430 --> 00:10.141
Guess who's here.
Your dad!

00:10.224 --> 00:13.895
[Chuckles] He drove his R.V.
all the way up from Cocoa Beach.

00:13.978 --> 00:16.272
Hey, Son, working hard?

00:16.397 --> 00:18.399
He's gonna say “Hardly
working.” [Chuckles]

00:18.482 --> 00:21.360
I meant to tell you
he was driving out.

00:21.485 --> 00:23.237
Did he say it?
Oh, yeah.

00:23.321 --> 00:26.699
- Good kid.
- He wasn't supposed to
show up for a few more days.

00:26.782 --> 00:29.452
Well, guess what he brought us.

00:29.535 --> 00:32.121
A dog... to keep.

00:32.205 --> 00:34.373
Yes! Yes.

00:34.457 --> 00:38.669
Yes, I should have told Claire
about the dog, and I was going to.

00:38.753 --> 00:41.464
But I was just waiting for her
to be in the right mood.

00:43.382 --> 00:45.542
Actually, I did get one right mood
a couple nights ago,

00:45.593 --> 00:49.096
but I cashed that in
for something else.

00:49.180 --> 00:53.893
- Am I in trouble?
- Oh, really, really big.

00:54.018 --> 00:56.646
Okay, I'm a little scared.
How bad is this? Oh, well...

00:56.729 --> 01:00.107
We have a new rule— no
sleeping in the bedroom. [Chuckles]

01:05.154 --> 01:08.324
Mr. Pritchett.
Uh, Ben— Ben Dugan.

01:08.407 --> 01:10.928
I went to high school with Mitch.
We were in the drama club together.

01:10.952 --> 01:12.662
That's right.
Yeah.

01:12.745 --> 01:15.248
Geez, I didn't recognize you
without that old—guy makeup on.

01:15.331 --> 01:17.959
You know, you and Mitch knocked
The <i>Sunshine Boys</i> out of the park.

01:18.042 --> 01:20.962
Mitch was really great in that.
I always thought he should be an actor.

01:21.045 --> 01:23.756
Yeah, he's got a real job now.
He's a lawyer. How about you?

01:23.881 --> 01:26.634
Still acting.
Fantastic.

01:26.717 --> 01:29.557
Actually, it's exciting. I'm in a new
movie, <i>Maple Drive.</i> Just came out.

01:29.637 --> 01:32.098
You're kidding me. Look at me.
I know somebody famous.

01:32.181 --> 01:34.308
Uh, anyway, I got to go.

01:34.433 --> 01:37.061
Great to see you. Good
to see you too. Yeah.

01:37.144 --> 01:39.563
Kid's a movie star.

01:39.689 --> 01:41.565
Hey, how'd it go in there?
No cavities.

01:41.691 --> 01:44.568
And I got a free toothbrush.
Hey, you want to go to the movies?

01:44.694 --> 01:47.238
I just heard about a good one.
But I'm supposed to be in school.

01:47.321 --> 01:49.675
Well, you're supposed to floss
too, but you got away with that one.

01:49.699 --> 01:51.659
Come on. Let's go.

01:51.742 --> 01:53.661
<i>[ Jay]
One of the greatest days of my life...</i>

01:53.744 --> 01:57.498
was when my old man sprung me
from school and took me to the track.

01:57.581 --> 01:59.792
I wanted to do the same
type of thing for Manny,

01:59.875 --> 02:03.879
plus I figured when Gloria heard
about it, maybe it pays off in the bedroom.

02:05.298 --> 02:07.341
I wonder if that's
why my old man did it.

02:08.342 --> 02:10.261
Oh, crap.

02:10.344 --> 02:12.888
<i>[ Dad ] Your mother-in-law
just had to have the dog.</i>

02:12.972 --> 02:15.016
Turns out she's allergic.

02:15.099 --> 02:18.978
And the pet store didn't have a grace
period or a return policy or anything?

02:19.061 --> 02:20.938
I got him from the pound.

02:21.022 --> 02:25.526
<i>Was there a twister in Kansas?
'Cause there's a house in my drive way.</i>

02:25.651 --> 02:29.155
Welcome home, Mr. Dunphy.
Uh, always a pleasure, Mr. Dunphy.

02:29.238 --> 02:32.908
Indeed it is, Mr. Dunphy.
Place it there.

02:32.992 --> 02:36.120
<i>- Oh, I shall. I shall.
—</i> I miss this. <i>Get in</i> here.

02:36.203 --> 02:37.663
<i>[ Phil]
My dad is awesome.</i>

02:37.747 --> 02:41.000
He's awesome. He's always up.
He's always happy.

02:41.083 --> 02:44.337
I mean, he and I are best buds.
We're like two peas in a pod.

02:44.420 --> 02:47.923
Or Siamese twins.
Or a snake with two heads.

02:48.049 --> 02:50.968
They've actually been all
those things for Halloween. Yeah.

02:51.052 --> 02:53.387
Oy. This must be Scout, huh?

02:53.471 --> 02:57.183
I should warn you. He sheds. I made the mistake
of letting him sleep with me on the road.

02:57.266 --> 03:00.603
Now my sheets look like two
bigfoots did it. Pardon the language.

03:00.728 --> 03:03.981
<i>[ Chuckles ] How's Mom?</i>
Speaking of big feet, eh?

03:04.065 --> 03:06.275
She's on a cruise
with her girlfriends,

03:06.359 --> 03:08.319
some of which are not
totally unattractive.

03:08.402 --> 03:11.572
Oh, that reminds me.
She sent some gifts for the kids.

03:11.655 --> 03:13.574
Um, I will be right back.

03:13.657 --> 03:16.577
- You three get better acquainted.
- Will do!

03:16.702 --> 03:18.204
Bye!
Will do!

03:18.287 --> 03:20.956
I cannot believe you got a dog
without consulting me.

03:21.040 --> 03:23.084
This was a major family decision.

03:23.209 --> 03:24.668
It was wrong.
Yeah.

03:24.794 --> 03:25.961
And I'm sorry.
Mmm.

03:26.045 --> 03:28.047
But we have talked about
getting a dog for years,

03:28.130 --> 03:29.810
and you're the only one
who wasn't into it.

03:29.882 --> 03:32.176
Because I knew that I would be
the one taking care of it.

03:32.301 --> 03:33.761
That's not true.
Uh...

03:33.886 --> 03:36.222
No, we will all help.
Mm-hmm?

03:36.305 --> 03:39.892
This is a great chance to
teach the kids responsibility.

03:39.975 --> 03:42.645
That is exactly what you said
about Luke's paper route.

03:49.443 --> 03:51.404
<i>([ Man ] J“ Hey, hey)</i>

03:51.487 --> 03:55.574
<i>(Y Hey, hey Hey, hey)</i>

03:55.658 --> 03:58.828
<i>Y Hey, hey Heyw</i>

04:01.914 --> 04:04.792
Hello?
;; [ Suspenseful ]

04:04.875 --> 04:07.169
<i>Is anyone in there?</i>

04:11.173 --> 04:13.509
[ Gasps ]

04:16.679 --> 04:19.390
[ Breathing Heavily ]

04:19.473 --> 04:21.767
Red's a good color on you.

04:21.851 --> 04:24.061
[Screaming ]

04:24.186 --> 04:26.564
[Whimpers ]
<i>[Knife Slash/fig ]</i>

04:26.647 --> 04:28.566
It's just a movie.

04:28.649 --> 04:30.568
<i>[ Haley]
Oh, he's so cute.</i>

04:30.651 --> 04:35.489
Look at his little face. I always
wanted a dog. Thanks, Grandpa.

04:35.573 --> 04:37.843
Okay, but remember, having a dog
is a major responsibility.

04:37.867 --> 04:40.035
<i>Everyone in the family
has to pitch in.</i>

04:40.119 --> 04:43.122
- Can do, Mrs. D.
- Not you, Dylan.

04:43.205 --> 04:45.291
Oh, phew. 'Cause I got
a lot on my plate right now.

04:45.374 --> 04:47.626
<i>[ Phil] Hey, look
who's here. Uncle Cam.</i>

04:47.710 --> 04:51.005
Hey, we heard about the new
addition and we had to come right over.

04:51.088 --> 04:55.217
Cameron, so good to see
you again. Now that is a shirt.

04:55.301 --> 04:57.941
Oh, well, thank you, Frank. I
get 'em online. I'll send you a link.

04:57.970 --> 05:00.931
Oh, well, at home, I smoke
sausages. I'll send you a link.

05:01.015 --> 05:02.641
<i>[Laughs]
Classic.</i>

05:02.725 --> 05:05.394
<i>And this must be Lily.
Oh,</i> yes.

05:05.519 --> 05:07.372
Aww! She just couldn't
wait to meet the new doggy.

05:07.396 --> 05:11.317
I think she's good right here. Let me get
in there and get some of that doggyness.

05:11.442 --> 05:13.819
Oh, there it is.
Haley.

05:13.944 --> 05:15.488
There <i>it is.
I gotta go.</i>

05:15.613 --> 05:18.616
What's wrong? That was
Brian. He just quit the band.

05:18.741 --> 05:22.953
What? Why? He's moving to
Portland. His parents got back together.

05:23.078 --> 05:24.997
Oh, that sucks.
I know.

05:25.080 --> 05:27.400
<i>[ Dylan ] Now we 're gonna
have to cancel the gig tomorrow.</i>

05:27.458 --> 05:29.376
Maybe you can find
another drummer.

05:29.460 --> 05:31.670
No. I think it's
too late for that now.

05:31.754 --> 05:33.339
I play drums.

05:33.464 --> 05:36.091
Huh? <i>Well, / mean, /
haven 'z' played in a While,</i>

05:36.175 --> 05:41.222
since Lily's come along,
but if you're in a jam, I can jam.

05:41.305 --> 05:45.434
Well, I totally would, but I'm not sure we
like the same sorts of music, you know?

05:45.518 --> 05:47.579
What, because I'm gay, I'm just
gonna want to play show tunes?

05:47.603 --> 05:49.730
No, because you're old.

05:50.940 --> 05:52.900
Wow. That hurt more, Dylan.

05:52.983 --> 05:55.528
Give him a chance.
It's better than canceling.

05:55.611 --> 05:59.657
You're right. I don't want to lose
the deposit on that fog machine.

05:59.740 --> 06:01.700
Okay. Let's do it.

06:01.784 --> 06:04.995
<i>I used to be a music teacher, but I
gave that up as soon as Lily came along.</i>

06:05.079 --> 06:07.140
Yes. Well, we just felt that
it was really important...

06:07.164 --> 06:09.124
that one of us stayed home
to raise her, so...

06:09.208 --> 06:11.311
Yeah, and that's not a judgment
on other people's choices.

06:11.335 --> 06:15.839
It's just that we happen to be a
very traditional family. Mm-hmm.

06:15.923 --> 06:19.843
Yes, that's what the disabled lesbian
shaman who blessed Lily's room said too.

06:25.307 --> 06:27.226
How you doin', buddy?
[Whimpers]

06:27.309 --> 06:29.979
All right, relax.

06:31.689 --> 06:33.774
<i>[ Sobbing ]</i>

06:37.861 --> 06:40.948
<i>[ Wailing]</i>

06:44.660 --> 06:46.662
Oh, geez.

06:51.709 --> 06:54.628
<i>I am telling you, Phil,
the man was crying.</i>

06:54.712 --> 06:56.922
That is impossible.
My dad is the happiest guy on earth.

06:57.006 --> 06:58.692
It probably just sounded like
he was crying.

06:58.716 --> 07:01.385
Have you heard the noise he
makes when he gets out of a chair?

07:01.468 --> 07:04.597
No. I know what I heard. I think this
has something to do with your mom.

07:04.722 --> 07:07.474
What? Yeah, he came
here alone. Think about it.

07:07.600 --> 07:11.478
She's on a cruise. Yeah, and they
never take separate vacations, so...

07:12.855 --> 07:15.608
No. No, if something was wrong,
my dad would tell me about it.

07:15.733 --> 07:18.902
No, Phil, he wouldn't, because you
guys never actually talk about anything.

07:18.986 --> 07:21.906
We talk all the time. He crank calls
me at work, like, three times a week.

07:22.031 --> 07:23.949
Crank calls don't count.
Counts for fun.

07:24.033 --> 07:27.911
No, honestly, I think that you should
find out what's going on with your dad.

07:27.995 --> 07:31.957
It's going to be nothing.
My dad isn't like your dad.

07:32.041 --> 07:34.126
There's nothing
deep and dark inside.

07:34.209 --> 07:37.588
His hard candy shell
is just hiding more candy.

07:37.671 --> 07:41.675
<i>- [ Scout Barks]</i> - I think he
wants to go out. Good boy.

07:41.800 --> 07:46.221
Smart dog. I hate to break it to
you, but I think all dogs can do that.

07:46.305 --> 07:47.806
I'm gonna play outside.

07:47.890 --> 07:50.434
- [ Crash ] _ Om!

07:50.517 --> 07:53.479
Uh! What happened?

07:53.562 --> 07:55.481
<i>[ Cameron ]
Okay.</i>

07:55.564 --> 07:57.900
Should I just play
a little something?

07:57.983 --> 08:01.362
Yeah. But, you know, if it
doesn't work out, don't feel bad.

08:01.445 --> 08:05.574
Well, hopefully this is—
This is like riding a bicycle,

08:05.658 --> 08:08.077
<i>and it'll all come back to me.</i>

08:08.202 --> 08:10.829
(3) [ Bass Drum]
That's the loud one.

08:10.913 --> 08:13.916
So... here we go.

08:29.223 --> 08:31.141
Hmm.

08:31.225 --> 08:33.268
<i>Oh, silly me.</i>

08:33.352 --> 08:35.854
I had the sticks
in the wrong hands.

08:53.038 --> 08:54.832
Wow.

08:54.915 --> 08:58.001
Dude, you should
label those sticks.

08:58.085 --> 08:59.670
[ Clicks Tongue ]

08:59.753 --> 09:02.005
<i>[ Doorbell Ringing ]</i>

09:02.089 --> 09:04.091
[ Ringing Continues]

09:04.174 --> 09:06.802
Is that the alarm? Has our
perimeter been breached?

09:06.885 --> 09:09.513
It's not the alarm.
The doorbell won't stop ringing.

09:09.638 --> 09:11.473
Maybe a demon is
ringing it. Not a demon.

09:11.557 --> 09:14.727
IAy! <i>Who keeps ringing
the doorbell?</i>

09:14.852 --> 09:17.563
We're pretty sure it's
a demon. Oh, yeah?

09:17.688 --> 09:19.356
[ Ringing Stops ]
[ Grunts ] There.

09:19.440 --> 09:21.400
If it were a demon,
it would keep on ringing.

09:21.483 --> 09:24.695
Not if he's already inside.
I'm getting a weapon.

09:24.778 --> 09:27.030
What were you thinking?

09:27.114 --> 09:30.159
Who takes a little boy to a
horror movie? That's <i>loco,</i> Jay.

09:30.242 --> 09:32.327
This is no big deal.
You want scary?

09:32.411 --> 09:35.539
When I was his age, I lived
through the Cuban Missile Crisis.

09:35.622 --> 09:37.750
I slept with a butter knife
under my pillow...

09:37.833 --> 09:40.377
in case I had to fight
some Soviet colonel.

09:40.461 --> 09:43.589
Why would they send a
Soviet colonel to get a little boy?

09:43.672 --> 09:46.258
Because I could identify
every commie plane.

09:46.341 --> 09:48.469
What are we talking about?

09:48.552 --> 09:50.792
Look, all I'm saying, being
scared is part of growing up.

09:50.846 --> 09:54.892
Manny will get over this.
It builds character.

09:54.975 --> 09:59.104
I'll take the first watch. You
two might as well get some rest.

09:59.188 --> 10:01.440
It's gonna be a long night.

10:03.317 --> 10:05.319
Character.

10:06.779 --> 10:08.238
Dad?

10:08.363 --> 10:10.616
<i>Come on in! It's open!</i> Hey!

10:10.699 --> 10:13.076
Ah, don't tell me.
You need a cup of sugar.

10:13.160 --> 10:15.913
[Chuckles]
Nah. Just, uh...

10:15.996 --> 10:20.125
I was just wondering,
I don't know, uh...

10:20.209 --> 10:21.877
Anything on the old noodle?

10:21.960 --> 10:25.589
Other than a bad toupee? I'm
kidding, of course. This is my real hair.

10:25.714 --> 10:29.134
Well, okay. Wait a minute. I
want to ask you something.

10:29.218 --> 10:32.513
Am I putting you in a bad
position with this whole dog thing?

10:32.638 --> 10:35.724
Claire seemed a little put out.
Oh, don't worry about it.

10:35.849 --> 10:40.354
Claire didn't like me at first either.
I can't blame her. Dismissed!

10:40.437 --> 10:44.650
[Chuckles]
Oh, Dad, um, you know what? I, uh...

10:44.733 --> 10:48.987
Claire saw something, and
she'd kill me if I— if I didn't ask.

10:49.071 --> 10:51.573
What is it?

10:54.618 --> 10:58.413
Would you wear pants to
breakfast, for crying out loud?

10:58.539 --> 11:01.416
You got me again. Right
in the funny bone. All right.

11:01.500 --> 11:03.544
Come on, Scout. Let go of it.
[ Growling ]

11:03.627 --> 11:05.796
No, no, no! Oh!

11:05.879 --> 11:08.006
Dog. Look at this.

11:08.090 --> 11:10.342
How did he get
a hold of your bra?

11:10.425 --> 11:13.512
Well, uh, we were out on a date,
and he has a really nice car, so...

11:13.595 --> 11:15.973
How do you think?
He got it out of the laundry basket.

11:16.056 --> 11:18.267
Can't take my eyes
off that dog for a second.

11:18.350 --> 11:20.811
- Why don't you just
keep him in the crate?
- I tried that.

11:20.894 --> 11:23.981
He figured out how to get out. I
thought you were dealing with your dad.

11:24.064 --> 11:26.024
Oh, yeah,
I did. He's fine, so...

11:26.108 --> 11:29.486
Whoa! You got that from
a two-minute conversation?

11:29.570 --> 11:34.616
I... asked him point-blank if he
was okay. He said he was. So I just...

11:34.700 --> 11:37.911
Just swapped some jokes
and moved on.

11:37.995 --> 11:40.372
Phil, the man needs more
of a push than that.

11:40.455 --> 11:44.459
<i>Look, if he wants to
talk to me about it, he will.</i>

11:44.543 --> 11:46.420
Geez, someone's panties
are in a bunch.

11:46.545 --> 11:49.256
I thought I was showing
concern and— No. Right there.

11:49.339 --> 11:52.384
Oh, my God!
That damn dog!

11:52.467 --> 11:55.220
<i>Guys, little help?</i>

11:55.304 --> 11:58.682
I have to go to the bathroom,
and I'm not gonna do it in here.

12:01.143 --> 12:04.855
<i>♪ J' [ Drumming ]</i>

12:06.690 --> 12:10.944
- Hey, I got Chinese.
- Sweet! I'm starving.

12:11.028 --> 12:15.282
- Oh, we have guests.
- Yeah. Hey. We're just
having a little jam session.

12:15.365 --> 12:18.327
<i>You know Dylan.
This is Craig. This is Neil.</i>

12:18.410 --> 12:20.746
<i>I'll always remember him
as the stranger holding my baby.</i>

12:20.829 --> 12:23.290
Can I talk to you
in the kitchen for a second?

12:23.373 --> 12:26.627
Yeah. Hey, guys, let's, uh—
Let's just take five.

12:26.710 --> 12:28.754
What's <i>up</i> with <i>27 Jump Street?</i>

12:28.837 --> 12:31.924
Oh, well, their drummer quit and
I'm gonna fill in for him tomorrow night.

12:32.007 --> 12:35.135
No, no. We have Pepper's apres-ski
fondue party tomorrow night, Cam.

12:35.218 --> 12:37.137
Oh, no.

12:37.220 --> 12:40.241
So you'll just have to tell your band that
they're gonna have to find someone else.

12:40.265 --> 12:43.265
You know what? No. I'm not gonna let
these fellas down. I made a commitment.

12:43.310 --> 12:45.270
You made two commitments, okay?

12:45.354 --> 12:47.773
And you know how Pepper is.
Everything has to be perfect.

12:47.856 --> 12:49.983
He gets mad if you
don't wear a big sweater.

12:50.108 --> 12:53.308
Yeah, I remember. I got so hot last year,
I almost went face down in the gruyere.

12:53.362 --> 12:55.364
So I'm going by myself,
is that what you're saying?

12:55.447 --> 12:58.116
[ Exhales]
I just feel like I kind of need this.

12:58.200 --> 13:00.911
To round out
your college applications?

13:00.994 --> 13:03.622
It's just that because
I'm always home with Lin...

13:03.705 --> 13:05.958
I just feel like I'm going
a little bit stir-crazy.

13:06.041 --> 13:08.921
Look at the den. Every time I
finish painting it, I start all over again.

13:08.961 --> 13:11.797
It's like the Golden Gate Bridge.

13:11.880 --> 13:14.424
I'm gonna go back to jamming.

13:17.678 --> 13:19.763
[Grunts, Screams]

13:21.556 --> 13:23.725
Yeah, we gotta fix this.
Ay-

13:27.479 --> 13:31.900
<i>♪ J' [ Speakers: Rock ]
[ Chattering ]</i>

13:33.568 --> 13:36.613
Hey, what's with the big sweater
at a concert? Is that a gay thing?

13:36.697 --> 13:40.283
No, Dad. It's for my friend
Pepper's aprés-ski fondue...

13:40.367 --> 13:42.744
Yeah. Yeah, it's a gay thing.

13:42.828 --> 13:45.956
Hope they start soon. I don't
think Scout likes to be left alone.

13:47.749 --> 13:49.501
You love the dog.

13:49.584 --> 13:51.795
No, I don't love the dog.
I love my couch.

13:51.878 --> 13:54.840
And the dog was looking at it
like it was a giant sausage.

13:54.923 --> 13:57.092
Good news, you two.
You're getting your driveway back.

13:57.217 --> 13:59.761
I'm hitting the open road in
the morning. Oh, already?

13:59.886 --> 14:01.763
Yeah. Anxious to get
home and see Mom, huh?

14:01.847 --> 14:03.825
No, I'm just gonna drive
wherever the wind blows me,

14:03.849 --> 14:05.559
which is usually
into the next lane.

14:05.642 --> 14:07.561
<i>[Alex] Can we get
some sodas, Grandpa .?</i>

14:07.644 --> 14:09.980
Okay, but just one. I'm driving.
Come on. [Alex Chuckles ]

14:12.274 --> 14:16.153
He's not going home? He's never been away from
my mom for longer than a doctor's appointment.

14:16.236 --> 14:18.155
Honey, I know.
I told you.

14:18.238 --> 14:20.550
I always felt bad for people
with emotionally distant fathers.

14:20.574 --> 14:22.034
It turns out I'm one of 'em.

14:22.117 --> 14:25.412
It's a miracle
I didn't end up a stripper.

14:25.495 --> 14:27.414
Hey. Thanks, everybody,
for coming out.

